concept_explanation.resolvers:
**Spring for GraphQL resolvers:**

```java
// src/main/resources/graphql/schema.graphqls
// type Query { product(id: ID!): Product  products: [Product!]! }
// type Mutation { createProduct(input: CreateProductInput!): Product! }

@Controller
public class ProductController {

    private final ProductService productService;

    // Maps to: type Query { product(id: ID!): Product }
    @QueryMapping
    public Product product(@Argument String id) {
        return productService.findById(id);  // null = field returns null
    }

    // Maps to: type Query { products(category: Category): [Product!]! }
    @QueryMapping
    public List<Product> products(
            @Argument(name = "category") String category) {
        return productService.findByCategory(category);
    }

    // Maps to: type Mutation { createProduct(input: CreateProductInput!): Product! }
    @MutationMapping
    public Product createProduct(@Argument CreateProductInput input) {
        return productService.create(input);
    }

    // Maps to: type Product { reviews: [Review!]! } — field resolver
    // Called for EACH product that has 'reviews' in the query
    @SchemaMapping(typeName = "Product", field = "reviews")
    public List<Review> reviews(Product product) {
        return reviewService.findByProductId(product.getId());
    }

    // Or shorthand:
    @SchemaMapping  // method name 'reviews' on type inferred from parent class context
    public List<Review> reviews(Product product) { ... }
}
```

